Interface LogProperty.PropertyValue<T>

Type Parameters:
T - property type.
All Superinterfaces:
Supplier<LogProperty.Result<T>>
All Known Subinterfaces:
LogProperty.RequiredResult<T>, LogProperty.Result<T>, LogProperty.Result.Success<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
LogProperty.Result.Error, LogProperty.Result.Missing, LogProperty.Result.Success.PropertySuccess, LogProperty.Result.Success.ValueSuccess
Enclosing interface:
LogProperty
public static interface LogProperty.PropertyValue<T> extends Supplier<LogProperty.Result<T>>
A supplier of a property result. Can be lazy but does not have to be. A non lazy PropertyValue is LogProperty.Result.

    • override

      default T override(@Nullable T replacement)
      Overrides the result with a value if it is not null regardless if the original Result is an error or not. This overrides even an error result from get()! This is equivalent to replacement == null ? value.value() : replacement;.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
